  <intervention>
    <intervention_type>Procedure</intervention_type>
    <intervention_name>blood sampling and brachial artery ultrasound</intervention_name>
    <description>Intravenous blood sampling will be performed before and 15 seconds, 30 seconds, 1,2,5,10,and 30 minutes following an ischemic stimulus (inflation of a blood pressure cuff to suprasystolic pressure for 5 minutes)
Brachial artery ultrasound imaging will be performed before and 1 minute after a 5 minute ischemic stimulus, to assess endothelium-dependent vasodilation of the brachial artery.
Following completion of blood sampling, an additional &quot;resting&quot; image of the brachial artery will be obtained. Sub-lingual nitroglycerin will be administered, and the artery will be imaged again after 3 minutes, to assess endothelium-independent vasodilation.</description>
    <arm_group_label>1</arm_group_label>
  </intervention>
